Reports that spread for a few weeks by local sources in the province of South Kivu on the presence of the Burundian army on Congolese territory are becoming clearer. However, from the Congolese government side, no official communication has yet been made. It is the Burundian rebel group of the Resistance for a Rule of Law in Burundi (RED-Tabara) which claims to have fought on Sunday January 02, 2022 with the National Defence Forces of Burundi (FDNB) and Imbonerakure which is the youth league of the National Council for the Defence of Democracy- Force for the Defence of Democracy, ruling party in Burundi. According to a short press release posted on its social networks, the rebel group Red-Tabara indicates that these clashes left at least 10 dead and around twenty wounded on the enemy side, which are soldiers of the Burundian army in the highlands of South Kivu in Eastern DRC. "We fought this afternoon in Gashenyo and Kitembe in the highlands in South Kivu, DRC, against the National Defence Forces of Burundi (FDNB) and Imbonerakure of the National Council for the Defence of Democracy - Force for the Defence of Democracy (CNDD-FDD). “At least 10 dead and twenty wounded on the enemy side ”, the tweet from the rebel group reads . Reports from local sources say that on December 20, a dozen armed men crossed the Luvungi border from Burundi, according to some members of the provincial government of South Kivu. During the same period, the Red Tabara, a Burundian rebel group, also present in the region, claims to have exchanged fire with the Burundian loyalist forces at the border. However, Congolese officials remain mum on the presence of Burundian soldiers on the Congolese territory and up to the time of the press reports not a single word has been said officially.  --Channel Africa--